1
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:05,117
<i>(With English accent)</i>
"Renstjärnas gata thirty-one?"

2
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,269
Thirty-one. Renstjärnas gata?

3
00:02:07,303 --> 00:02:09,303
It's right over there!

4
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:44,551
But dear child! What a mess!

5
00:02:44,763 --> 00:02:46,953
What will dad say when he sees this?

6
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:52,031
Sit there.

7
00:02:53,593 --> 00:02:55,680
No! I just told you!

8
00:02:55,703 --> 00:02:58,738
Don't soil the nice dress that mommy has bought!

9
00:02:59,765 --> 00:03:02,644
It was so clean and nice.

10
00:03:02,712 --> 00:03:05,758
Sit still and watch the other children play.

11
00:03:05,994 --> 00:03:06,853
No!

12
00:03:06,995 --> 00:03:09,030
If you are acting like this -

13
00:03:09,055 --> 00:03:11,055
we're headed straight home!

14
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,691
You are getting dirty all the time.

15
00:03:12,722 --> 00:03:15,954
We are going home to bed.

16
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:16,994
All done.

17
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:28,230
- Hey!
- Hello.

18
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:30,357
Fill it up.

19
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:34,275
Help!

20
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:39,879
- Is somebody calling for help?
- It's always a racket around here.

21
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:44,512
- Heeeelp!
- What hoodlums are they?

22
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:48,514
I don't know. They're always at it.

23
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:52,958
Don't pour the gas in my pocket!

24
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:56,750
Help... Help!

25
00:04:59,416 --> 00:05:01,596
You goddamn...

26
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:19,757
Help! I've broke my leg! Help!

27
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:30,913
- Boys!
- Wino!

28
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:38,793
Help!

29
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,727
Help! I'm stuck!

30
00:05:43,693 --> 00:05:45,809
<i>(In Finnish)</i>
- Who is that?
- He's asking for help

31
00:05:45,929 --> 00:05:48,096
<i>(In Finnish)</i>
- Noo.. No, we can't help him.

32
00:05:48,216 --> 00:05:52,600
I'm stuck.. I've fallen.. Help!

33
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:57,674
<i>(Swedish student graduation song)</i>

34
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:06,790
Help!

35
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:11,754
Thanks.

36
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:22,800
- Hey! You!
- Hey buddy!

37
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:26,396
- My leg is broken
- Heeey!

38
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:32,477
- You have a drink!
- No, thanks. My foot hurts so bad.

39
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:38,952
<i>(Singing)</i>
In the spring sun

40
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,298
You're going to meet my old lady! -

41
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:43,310
If she can trust you.

42
00:06:45,589 --> 00:06:48,051
My foot hurts so bad. I live over here. -

43
00:06:48,076 --> 00:06:50,076
Can you please help me?

44
00:06:50,101 --> 00:06:52,069
Your foot hurts? You shouldn't be -

45
00:06:52,114 --> 00:06:54,114
walking around then! Just a second...

46
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:59,359
I'll help you. If I could just... Oh!

47
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:03,664
This is no good! I've got to get some help!

48
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:11,633
- If I can have the balloon.
- Of course. Here. Please get some help.

49
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:15,873
Heeelp! Heeelp!

50
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,478
Help... Help!

51
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:08,553
Uh... Look at that. This is tire-some. Heh.

52
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:17,274
- Nice weather tonight.
- I think my foot is broken.

53
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,233
Can you help me?

54
00:09:19,677 --> 00:09:21,710
Gosh! Your leg is broken and you're stuck!

55
00:09:21,755 --> 00:09:23,755
Of course we will help you.

56
00:09:23,869 --> 00:09:26,019
I live just up here.

57
00:09:26,287 --> 00:09:30,048
- How can I help?
- I'm stuck.

58
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:34,229
- Pull!
- Remove that tire.

59
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:38,473
- Oh hey!
- Careful!

60
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:44,754
- Careful.
- I can turn around.

61
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:47,753
- There!
- Yes, there.

62
00:09:47,873 --> 00:09:49,919
Mind your foot.

63
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:57,316
- I'll run and get an ambulance!
- Yes, do that!

64
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,856
- There, this is good. This is all right.

65
00:10:21,052 --> 00:10:22,372
- I'll help you.

66
00:10:22,403 --> 00:10:25,479
- Thanks.
- There, there.

67
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:32,670
- Shall I take the hat?
- Thanks.

68
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:37,161
- Are you all right?
- Please sitt, miss. In the couch.

69
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:41,115
Thank you.

70
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:03,480
I guess it's the nursing home from now on.

71
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:21,030
- What time is it?
- The time?

72
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:28,115
- A quarter past two.
- A handsome watch.

73
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,510
It chimes too.

74
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:36,674
I got it from my father today.

75
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:41,198
I got a similar clock by my father once.

76
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:44,590
But I gave it away to a beautiful girl.

77
00:12:47,214 --> 00:12:53,482
- It's called something else...
- Can you ask Herbert about that?

78
00:12:54,360 --> 00:13:00,630
No, he's in bed. He was asleep. He didn't hear me there.

79
00:13:05,928 --> 00:13:08,879
- Hey, you.
- Hey.

80
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:13,239
- May I sit by the window?
- Yes.

81
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:19,834
- Is this all right?
- Yes. Thank you, nurse. Thanks.

82
